canonical:
  title: 晉州山水圖
  author: 鄭與齡
  language: lzh
  text: 數點靑山枕碧湖公言此是晉陽圖水邊草屋知多少中有吾廬畫也無
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 晉州山水圖
  author: 鄭與齡
  language: lzh
  text: 數點靑山枕碧湖。公言此是晉陽圖。水邊草屋知多少。中有吾廬畫也無。
korean:
  title: 진주 산수도
  author: 정여령
  language: kor
  text: |-
    두어 점 청산이 푸른 호수를 베개했구나
    공이 이르기를 이것이 진양의 그림이라네
    물가에 초가집 얼마인가
    그중에 내 집도 있으련만 그려졌는지 안 그려졌는지
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0220_020_0570&viewSync=OT
  footnotes:
  - key: '[주-D001]  : '
    value: 작자가 진주(晉州) 사람인데, 이지저(李之氐)의 집에 갔더니 마침 주인이 진주 산수도(晉州山水圖)를 내보이며, “진주는 자네의 고향이니 시(詩) 한 수를 쓰라.” 하므로 즉석에서 부른 것이다.
english:
  title: A Painting of Jinzhou Landscape
  author: Jeong Yeoryeong
  language: eng
  text: |-
    A few blue peaks cradle the emerald lake,
    And my friend declares: "This is Jinyang's painting."
    How many grass-thatched cottages line the water's edge?
    But tell me—is my own humble home sketched there, or left undrawn?
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Jinzhou (晉州) was the author's native place. The poem was composed impromptu when the author visited a friend who showed him this landscape painting and requested a poem, noting that Jinzhou was the author's hometown.
  - key: ''
    value: The name 'Jinyang' (晉陽) refers to an ancient name for the Jinzhou region.
